1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 39-04-10.10 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to veterans' number plates.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 39-04-10.10 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 39-04-10.10. North Dakota veterans' number plates.
7 1. The director may issue distinctive number plates to individuals eligible for interment in
8 the North Dakota veterans' cemetery. The director shall issue a number plate under
9 this section upon receiving:
10 a. Payment payment of all other fees required under this chapter for registration of a
11 motor vehicle;
12 b. Payment of an initial fee of fifteen dollars of which ten dollars is to be deposited in
13 the highway tax distribution fund and five dollars is to be deposited in the
14 veterans' cemetery maintenance fund unless for a plate issued to a veteran who
15 has been awarded the purple heart, then there is not an initial fee; and
16 c. Verification of subsequent payments of an annual surcharge of ten dollars paid to
17 the adjutant general unless for a plate issued to a veteran who has been
18 awarded the purple heart, then there is not an annual surcharge.
19 2. The department shall collect the fees and the ten dollar surcharge under this section.
20 The department shall report to the legislative assembly on the funds collected under
21 this section during each legislative session. The department shall pay the funds
22 collected under subdivisions b and c of subsection 1 to the adjutant general monthly,
23 who then, within ten days of receipt of the funds, shall deposit five dollars of each
24 initial fee in the veterans' cemetery maintenance fund and the ten dollar surcharge
